<MELItem itemNbr="49-94-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-49-94-01.1.2-49-94-01">
<Title>APU Oil Quantity Indication System</Title>
<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="A" repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)">
<Title>APU Available</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided APU oil quantity is verified adequate once each flight day.</Para>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Verify the APU oil quantity is adequate once each flight day using the APU oil level sight glass (AMM DDG 49-94-01).</Para>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="B" repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0">
<Title>APU Not Used</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Left AGCU operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>VFSG systems operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>APU is not used.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>EDTO beyond 180 minutes is not conducted.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceNote>
<Para>A VFSG system is considered to be operating normally if its associated status message (ELEC GEN SYS L1, L2, R1 or R2) is not displayed.</Para>
</MaintenanceNote>
<OperationNote>
<Para>For APU not available for engine start, start the first engine using the Ground Power Engine Start Supplementary Procedure.</Para>
</OperationNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
</DispatchItems>